Arthur<br><br>
Gerald Ford initiated the amnesty program in 1975, before the Fall of Saigon.  The only numbers that I could find estimate that only 20,000 of the 100,000 eligible draft evaders actually applied for amnesty.<br><br>
The reported purpose of the amnesty program was to provide a first step at reconcilliation for the American public.<br><br>
By the looks of things on this thread, doesn't seem like it worked very well, does it?
